# Research Questions\
\
- How has reef health changed in Cozumel between 2015 and 2024?\
- Does Cozumel follow the same trend as Mexico or other reef regions?\
- Do periods of high thermal stress coincide with declines in reef health?\
- Has the composition of coral families changed over time?\
\
---\
\
# Data Sources\
\
## NOAA Coral Reef Watch\
\
Daily Degree Heating Weeks (DHW) time series used as an indicator of accumulated thermal stress.\
\
## GBIF\
\
Georeferenced records of Cnidaria downloaded through the GBIF API and filtered geographically for Quintana Roo.\
\
## Healthy Reefs Initiative (HRI)\
\
Reef Health Index values manually compiled from the official Healthy Reefs Report Cards (2015, 2018, 2020, 2022 and 2024.\
\
---\
\
# Methodology\
\
## 1. Data acquisition\
\
- Download NOAA thermal stress data.\
- Query the GBIF API.\
- Build a structured Reef Health Index dataset.\
\
## 2. Data preparation\
\
- Convert date variables.\
- Filter observations between 2015 and 2024.\
- Handle missing values.\
- Select reef-building coral families.\
- Aggregate less frequent families into an **Others** category.\
\
## 3. Exploratory Data Analysis\
\
- Reef Health Index trends.\
- Thermal stress (DHW) evolution.\
- Coral family composition.\
- Comparison among Cozumel, Quintana Roo and Mexico.\
\
## 4. Visualization\
\
Visualizations include:\
\
- Reef Health Index trends by region.\
- Comparison between reef health and thermal stress.\
- Coral family composition over time.\
- Summary descriptive charts.\
