# Key Findings\
\
- Cozumel maintained one of the highest Reef Health Index values throughout most of the study period.\
- The 2024 bleaching event coincided with the highest accumulated thermal stress (DHW) observed during the analysis.\
- Coral family composition varied over time, although interpretation should consider differences in observation effort.\
- The analysis suggests temporal associations between thermal stress and reef condition but does not establish causal relationships.\
\
---\
\
# Limitations\
\
- GBIF records represent species occurrences rather than standardized ecological surveys.\
- Observation frequency depends on sampling effort and citizen science activity.\
- Reef Health Index values were manually digitized because no structured dataset is publicly available.\
- Results should be interpreted as exploratory rather than inferential.\
